title: Area Football: Ridgewood falls to Titans 42-6
text: Posted Oct. 17, 2015 at 12:01 AM Posted Oct. 17, 2015 at 12:01 AM CAMBRIDGE â€” The Ridgewood football team trailed by 28 at the intermission and went on to suffer a 42-6 loss to Annawan/Wethersfield. The Titans (7-1) took a 42-0 lead in the fourth quarter. Briar Greenman found Travis Kane for a five-yard pass for the Spartans (2-6) only TD with 7:28 left in the game. Greenman finished the night 12-for-23 for 151 yards. Jared Smith caught four passes for 74 yards and Kane had six catches for 64 yards. Caleb Sipp led the ground attack with 82 rushing yards on 14 attempts. The Register-Mail
